    <!-- Slide 2: Market Context -->
    <div class="slide">
        <h2>UAE Open Finance: Market at Inflection Point</h2>
        
        <div class="split-content">
            <div>
                <h3>Current Landscape</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>UAE Central Bank Open Finance Regulation issued in 2024, establishing regulatory framework</li>
                    <li>Total banking assets: AED 4.56 trillion (2024), creating substantial API-enabled opportunity</li>
                    <li>557,000 SMEs in UAE (2022), projected to reach 1 million by 2030—key target segment</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h3>Key Market Dynamics</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>329 active fintech companies (2024), demonstrating 128.5% growth since 2011</li>
                    <li>88% of UAE consumers used emerging payment methods in last year, indicating high digital readiness</li>
                    <li>UAE fintech market: USD 3.16B (2024) projected to USD 5.71B (2029), CAGR 12.56%</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div>
                <div class="chart-container">
